p,q
\left<a,x\right>
\mathbb{R}^{n}
\forall\, a\in\mathbb{R}^{n}:\,\Vert a\Vert_{q}=\max_{x\in\mathbb{R}^{n},\,\Vert x\Vert_{p}=1}\left<a,x\right>
v\in\mathbb{R}^{n}
\Vert v\Vert_{p}=1
\left<a,v\right>=\Vert a\Vert_{p}
v
\Vert v\Vert_{p}\leq1
\max_{x\in\mathbb{R}^{n},\,\Vert x\Vert_{p}=1}\left<a,x\right>\le\Vert a\Vert_{q}
\max_{x\in\mathbb{R}^{n},\,\Vert x\Vert_{p}=1}\left<a,x\right>=\max_{x\in\mathbb{R}^{n},\,\Vert x\Vert_{p}\leq1}\left<a,x\right>
x_k = \text{sgn } a_k |a_k|^{\frac{q}{p}}
x_k a_k = (\text{sgn } a_k) a_k |a_k|^{\frac{q}{p}} = |a_k|^{\frac{q}{p}+1} = |a_k|^q
\sum x_k a_k = \|a\|_q^q
\sum_k |x_k|^p = \sum_k |a_k|^q = \|a\|_q^q
\|x\|_p = \|a\|_q^{\frac{q}{p}}
\sum_k x_k a_k =\|a\|_q^{\frac{q}{p}} \|a\|_q^{q-\frac{q}{p}} = \|x\|_p \|a\|_q
v = \frac{1}{\|x\|_p} x
